This stage, known as nigredo, involves a descent into darkness, a confrontation with the shadow self, and the decomposition of the ego. It is a necessary phase of transformation where one must face and integrate the darker aspects of the psyche to progress towards wholeness. Spiritually, the Black Sun is linked to the idea of lumen naturae, the light of nature itself, which shines from the darkness. It resonates with mystical experiences across various traditions, such as the negative theology in Christianity, the void in Buddhism, and the black light of the Sufi Mystics.
